text.tspan: FIGS reported flat year-over-year revenue in Q1, reflecting challenging macro conditions. However, the company is seeing improved momentum in frequency starting mid-
March and continuing through April, leading to an acceleration embedded in Q2 revenue guidance of 3%-4% y/y growth.
FIGS raised its FY24 revenue guidance from (5)%-0% to (2)%-2%, incorporating better momentum and product cadence while still reflecting harder comps in Q3 and an
uncertain macro environment. The company is investing in global brand marketing and new product launches, which could drive higher growth over the long-term.
We are encouraged to see better than expected near-term trends and understand the strategy to lean into that momentum with additional brand marketing.
